Sentence.Text: Long ago, there was a kind orphan named Elli.
One day, Elli met an old lady holding a cooking pot. The lady looked tired.
Elli said, "You seem tired. Would you like some honey?" The lady ate some honey and felt better.
Then she said, "Now I will cook some porridge for you, little dear."
Surprised, Elli asked, "How can you cook porridge without any grain?"
The old lady put the cooking pot on the ground. Then she said, "Cook! Magic pot! Cook!" Right away, the cooking pot was full of porridge.
Then the lady said, "Stop! Magic pot! Stop!" The magic cooking pot stopped cooking.
The lady gave Elli a bowl of porridge. Elli ate the porridge and exclaimed, "Wow, this porridge is good!"
The old lady gave Elli the pot and said, "Take this pot home and use it wisely!" Elli happily thanked the lady.
At home, Elli cooked porridge with the magic pot. A boy next door saw what she was doing and wanted that magic pot.
As Elli slept, the boy stole the magic cooking pot. He took it home, and said, "Cook! Magic pot! Cook!" The magic pot was filled with porridge.
But the boy could not stop the pot. He forgot the magic words. He was afraid.
Seeking help, he ran to Elli. The magic cooking pot followed him.
Elli quickly yelled, "Stop! Magic pot! Stop!" The pot stopped right away. The boy felt ashamed.
Elli forgave the boy. From then on, Elli used the magic pot to cook porridge for the poor people in her village.
Long ago, there was a poor couple. One day, while cutting wheat, the husband heard someone yelling, "Help! Help!"
Looking around, the husband found a fairy stuck in a net. He freed the fairy from the net.

The fairy happily said, "Thank you!
I will grant you three wishes."
The husband was excited. He went home and told his wife everything.
Feeling hungry, the husband exclaimed, "I wish I had a big sausage!" Suddenly, a big sausage appeared on the plate.
The wife was not pleased with the wish. She yelled, "What a silly wish!"
Angry, the husband shouted, "I wish this sausage would stick in your mouth." At once, the sausage stuck in the wife's mouth.
The husband became afraid. He yelled, "Oh no, I wish the sausage would come back to the plate!" Right away, the sausage came back to the plate.
The couple wasted three wishes by having a silly argument. They learned a lesson: always respect each other.
